verbose_text: The hydrocyanic acid levels were expressed in mg/kg of dry matter using the following formula : (1) HCN (mgkg) = 0.54 (V2-V1) * 500250 * 1000M, V1 is the volume of ammonium thiocyanate required to neutralize the excess of silver nitrate in the sample test, V2 is the volume of ammonium thiocyanate required to neutralize the excess of silver nitrate in the blank test, M is the weight (gram) of the test sample.
